{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "ht-v5-dyndisc-clm-mirror-biweekly-1k",
    "name": "HT-DynDisc-CLM-Mirror-TimeEpoch-BiWeekly-1",
    "description": "HT v5 Enhanced: BTC CLM (digital asset) mirror passthrough + DynDisc2-style bi-weekly time epoch monitoring.\n\nKEY DIFFERENCES from HT v4:\n  1. Cash reserve seeds at $1,000 USD (CASH-PAM-1K PAM + CASH-RESERVE-SEED CSH marker)\n  2. AllocationDrift + LiquidityBuffer monitoringEventTimes = bi-weekly (every ~14 days) instead of monthly\n  3. Simulation monitoringTimes = same bi-weekly cross-cuts for full state visibility\n  4. BUYER_CASH_01 reference index tracks projected cash reserve trajectory from $1K seed\n  5. HURDLE_RATE_01 reference index (7.5%->8%->8.5%) baked for future invoice discounting\n  6. Mirror model initialNotionalPrincipal = $1,000 (matches PAM seed)\n  7. LiquidityBuffer min/target buffers scaled to seed cash level\n\nFLOW:\n  BTC price surges -> CLM drift detected at bi-weekly epoch\n  -> ad_btc01 fires PP (sells BTC, positive CLM payoff)\n  -> ad_btc01_mirror reads dollarPayoffCache -> injects exact $ into CASH-PAM-1K\n  -> lb_tr01 validates buffer health against outflows+T-bills at every epoch\n  -> BUYER_CASH_01 reference index tracks growing cash reserve curve\n\nEXPECTED BEHAVIOR vs HT v4:\n  HT v4: PP fires only at month-end (May-31, Jun-30)\n  HT v5: PP fires at FIRST bi-weekly epoch where allocation > 25%\n          -> May-15 (BTC=$68K, alloc=25.37%) triggers earlier rebalancing\n          -> Jun-15 (BTC=$85K) triggers second rebalancing\n          -> Mid-month zero-payoff PP events at all other bi-weekly epochs",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
